1
00:00:02,848 --> 00:00:06,956
If we say svarūp-siddhi, 
vastu-siddhi.

2
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:10,692
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj answered
this question once.

3
00:00:10,692 --> 00:00:13,400
Sometimes we hear examples
of someone

4
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:18,141
who is in a very high stage
of spiritual evolution,

5
00:00:18,141 --> 00:00:20,482
and then they fall
from that position.

6
00:00:20,782 --> 00:00:23,962
[Reincarnation of a Saint]

7
00:00:24,262 --> 00:00:27,352
Jaḍ Bhārat
is mentioned sometimes,

8
00:00:27,352 --> 00:00:30,749
who was at bhāva bhakti,
at this stage,

9
00:00:30,749 --> 00:00:35,894
and then a mother deer
had a miscarriage,

10
00:00:35,894 --> 00:00:39,334
with a little baby deer;
the mother died and

11
00:00:39,334 --> 00:00:44,751
the little baby deer was in the stream
in his ashram in the forest.

12
00:00:44,751 --> 00:00:47,321
So he has no attachment 
in the world,
 

13
00:00:47,321 --> 00:00:50,882
he’s in this high stage
of spiritual evolution,

14
00:00:50,882 --> 00:00:56,651
but he sees the little
helpless fawn (baby deer)

15
00:00:56,651 --> 00:01:00,233
and he’s senses,
he’s not heartless,

16
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:06,513
people who are evolved spiritually
are not heartless or insensitive,

17
00:01:06,513 --> 00:01:08,458
they are actually 
para duka duki,

18
00:01:08,458 --> 00:01:11,238
they are attentive 
to the suffering of others.

19
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:16,861
But they know the root cause
of all suffering is separation from Kṛṣṇa,

20
00:01:16,861 --> 00:01:19,916
whether it’s material suffering 
or spiritual suffering.

21
00:01:19,916 --> 00:01:24,804
The root cause of all suffering
is separation from Kṛṣṇa.

22
00:01:24,804 --> 00:01:29,298
At any rate, he takes
that little baby fawn into his ashram,

23
00:01:29,298 --> 00:01:34,273
and every day the fawn is …
a cute little deer 
 

24
00:01:34,273 --> 00:01:37,538
and he develops
some attachment for it.

25
00:01:37,538 --> 00:01:42,607
And he ends up leaving the world,
giving up this life

26
00:01:42,607 --> 00:01:44,742
with some attachment
to this little deer,

27
00:01:44,742 --> 00:01:47,340
and in his next life 
he becomes a deer.

28
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:52,403
But he is a deer like,
this is Christmas Eve,

29
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:53,074
and we are told,

30
00:01:53,074 --> 00:01:57,311
they never let poor Rudolph
join in any reindeer games.

31
00:01:57,311 --> 00:01:59,099
[Laughing]
 

32
00:01:59,099 --> 00:02:02,099
When Jaḍ Bhārat was a deer,

33
00:02:02,099 --> 00:02:05,746
he was not interested
in any reindeer games.

34
00:02:05,746 --> 00:02:08,171
He wasn’t seeking to admit …
we are told like,

35
00:02:08,171 --> 00:02:11,215
he was this deer—
he liked to hear sādhus,

36
00:02:11,215 --> 00:02:13,021
do Hari-kathā,
 

37
00:02:13,021 --> 00:02:15,905
with his deer head
he’s going like aććhā;

38
00:02:15,905 --> 00:02:18,889
he likes that,
he takes remnants of Vaiṣṇavas …

39
00:02:18,889 --> 00:02:22,042
he was a very serious deer.

40
00:02:22,042 --> 00:02:25,913
So, the point being 
that Guru Mahārāj said,

41
00:02:25,913 --> 00:02:28,665
when this is giving us 
an example,

42
00:02:28,665 --> 00:02:32,705
first delineate:
svarūp-siddhi, vastu-siddhi.

43
00:02:32,705 --> 00:02:34,422
That Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says,

44
00:02:34,422 --> 00:02:36,980
“From svarūp-siddhi, 
some deviation …
 

45
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:41,017
it’s possible to fall,
deviation is still possible.”

46
00:02:41,017 --> 00:02:42,721
What does svarūp-siddhi mean?

47
00:02:42,721 --> 00:02:45,986
It means when someone 
reaches the stage
 

48
00:02:45,986 --> 00:02:52,481
of awareness of their svarūp,
but not yet posted.

49
00:02:53,781 --> 00:02:55,491
And Guru Mahārāj’s example:

50
00:02:55,491 --> 00:03:00,468
“Someone may have qualified
to become a High Court judge—

51
00:03:00,468 --> 00:03:03,860
passed the test, got the stamp
of everything’s approved,

52
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:07,505
but not yet sitting in the court
and judging.”

53
00:03:07,505 --> 00:03:10,811
That’s vastu-siddhi—
he’s posted.

54
00:03:10,811 --> 00:03:16,840
Svarūp-siddhi—qualified,
but not yet posted.

55
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:20,757
And we are told,
as inconceivable as it may sound,

56
00:03:20,757 --> 00:03:23,258
between that awareness 
of qualification

57
00:03:23,258 --> 00:03:25,538
and qualification 
and being posted,
 

58
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:30,758
in that interim state
that deviation is possible,

59
00:03:30,758 --> 00:03:33,821
and it’s possible to fall
from that position.

